When shorting. You "borrow" XBT to sell them for USD. When longing. You "borrow" USD to sell them for XBT.However. positions are secured in XBT. What does it mean?When You're short and price goes against You. position is secured all time with the same amount of money (because You borrowed XBT and secure it with XBT).When You're long and price goes against You. position is secured with less and less amount of money (because You borrowed USD and secure it with XBT. but USD value of XBT is going down).Because in first case Your margin doesn't change and in second it does (it goes down along with price). longs are liquidated faster.
